    • Method Detail

      • setUsingOnlyBarcode

        void setUsingOnlyBarcode(boolean onlyBarcode)
        This method is called to indicate whether only barcode scanning will be performed. With this information, viewfinder can adapt its appearance for barcode-only scanning.
        Parameters:
        onlyBarcode - If true, only barcode scanning will be performed. If false, both barcode scanning and OCR scanning or only OCR scanning will be performed.

      • setProgressModifier

        void setProgressModifier(ProgressModifier modifier)
        This method is called to set appropriate progress modifier for current scan. Progress modifier can be used to recalculate current progress of scan.
        Parameters:
        modifier - Progress modifier

      • showProgress

        void showProgress(int progress)
        This method is called as a notification about scan progress. You may use progress modifier to adapt progress being sent. This method is called from background thread. Do not perform UI operations directly in this method, instead use Handler.
        Parameters:
        progress - Current scan progress from interval [0, 100].

      • setDefaultTarget

        void setDefaultTarget()
        This method is called to notify viewfinder that it should position itself into its default position. This method is called from background thread. Do not perform UI operations directly in this method, instead use Handler.

      • startProgressAnimation

        void startProgressAnimation()
        This method is called to notify viewfinder that it should start drawing progress animation. This method is called from background thread. Do not perform UI operations directly in this method, instead use Handler.

      • setPhotopayMode

        void setPhotopayMode(int mode)
        This method is called to notify viewfinder in which operating mode is scanning started.
        Parameters:
        mode - PhotoPay operating mode: can be PhotoPaySettings.RECOGNITION_MODE, PhotoPaySettings.RECOGNITION_TEST_MODE or PhotoPaySettings.DETECTION_TEST_MODE

      • setNewTarget

        void setNewTarget(net.photopay.geometry.Point uleft,
                net.photopay.geometry.Point uright,
                net.photopay.geometry.Point lleft,
                net.photopay.geometry.Point lright,
                int uleftIndex)
        This method is called to notify viewfinder that object has been detected so that it can draw itself around that object. This method is called from background thread. Do not perform UI operations directly in this method, instead use Handler.
        Parameters:
        uleft - Upper left position of the object's box.
        uright - Upper right position of the object's box.
        lleft - Lower left position of the object's box.
        lright - Lower right position of the object's box.
        uleftIndex - Which of given points is actual upper left point of object (in case of rotated image).

      • setPointSet

        void setPointSet(float[] points,
               boolean biColorPointSet)
        This method is called to notify viewfinder that object has been detected so that it can draw point of interest for this object. This method is called from background thread. Do not perform UI operations directly in this method, instead use Handler.
        Parameters:
        points - Array of coordinates for points of interest. Coordinates are packed in following way: x1,y1,x2,y2,...
        biColorPointSet - If true, this means the caller requested that odd points should be drawn in one color and even points in another color.

      • publishDetectionStatus

        void publishDetectionStatus(int detectionStatus,
                          boolean showProgress)
        This method is called to notify viewfinder about the status of detection. This method is called from background thread. Do not perform UI operations directly in this method, instead use Handler.
        Parameters:
        detectionStatus - The status of detection as defined in PaymentRecognizerDelegate
        showProgress - True if progress should be displayed on screen.

      • getView

        android.view.View getView()
        This method is called when adding viewfinder on top of camera surface. This method should return view that will be overlayed on camera.
        Returns:
        View that should be overlayed on camera.

      • setOrientation

        void setOrientation(Orientation orientation)
        This method is called when phone detects orientation change. Since camera activity is always in portrait, it is required only to rotate view.
        Parameters:
        orientation - The requested orientation.

      • shouldPutInsideCameraSurface

        boolean shouldPutInsideCameraSurface()
        if returned true, view obtained with getView will be layouted inside camera surface if returned false, view obtained with getView will be layouted over whole CameraPreview view

      • displayMessage

        void displayMessage(java.lang.CharSequence text)
        Viewfinder should display given message. This method is called from background thread. Do not perform UI operations directly in this method, instead use Handler.
        Parameters:
        text - Text to be displayed.

      • displayMessageImmediately

        void displayMessageImmediately(java.lang.CharSequence text)
        Viewfinder should display given message. Unlike displayMessage, this method is called from UI thread, so you can perform UI operations directly in this method.
        Parameters:
        text - Text to be displayed.

      • displayDebugStatus

        void displayDebugStatus(java.lang.CharSequence text)
        Viewfinder should display given debug message. This method is called from background thread. Do not perform UI operations directly in this method, instead use Handler.
        Parameters:
        text - Text to be displayed.

      • registerEventListener

        void registerEventListener(IViewFinder.EventListener listener)
        This method serves to register event listener which can handle messages. You can send message to listener by calling its onMessage method.
        Parameters:
        listener - Listener to be registered.

      • isAnimationInProgress

        boolean isAnimationInProgress()
        This method should return true if it wants to prevent finishing the activity while some animation is in progress.
        Returns:
        true if animation is in progress
